:{{A|VO chapter1 7 serval 315.ogg}} '''Serval:''' Yo! Evening, soldier!
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 soldierT 201.ogg}} '''Silvermane Guard:''' Are you the emergency engineers? I saw you guys hanging around. Did you find the problem?
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 serval 316.ogg}} '''Serval:''' Not yet, everything looks normal so far. I think the problem is stemming from the energy hub.
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 serval 317.ogg}} '''Serval:''' If you let us in we can do a routine service inspection... I've worked on various iterations of this type of installation...
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 soldierT 202.ogg}} '''Silvermane Guard:''' Haha, no, no, no, no... No can do! No one gets near the energy hub without the security captain's encryption key.
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 mar7th 231.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Uh, not even the supreme guardian?
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 soldierT 203.ogg}} '''Silvermane Guard:''' The supreme guardian...? Hey, no games, y'hear? No dice without the encryption key!
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 mar7th 232.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Darn, this guy's not stupid...
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 serval 318.ogg}} '''Serval:''' You need the encryption key, right? Which captain should I bother then?
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 soldierT 204.ogg}} '''Silvermane Guard:''' ...Captain Dunn's resting up ahead. Go and find him. If he grants you permission, I won't stand in your way.
:{{A|VO chapter1 7 serval 319.ogg}} '''Serval:''' Dunn... Dunn? Ha, why didn't you say so! No problem. We'll be back in a bit.
----
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
